<subSubSection id="6C719EFEF8207ABF8130B3D423758789" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D27F1B597556C4503EF062393F5B17C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D3C6A3850E15FB9308C149BB34D747DB" continue="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName id="6426901869EED3B378B18F8C7E426BD9" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Dias &amp; Zúñiga" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tortopus coreguaje" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreguaje">
<emphasis id="CEAE93E31A4BFA639B419CE3E994CA23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tortopus coreguaje</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="A34D79C882C7308564DB4F5CC0431F5C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, known from male imago and nymph, can be distinguished from all other species of the genus by the following combination of characters: In male imagos, 1) fore wing length 10.9-11.0 mm (male); 2) pale wings, veins translucent gray; 3) pedestal short with relatively large, straight and very long parastyli (Figs 
<figureCitation id="0DEBFE82D8A867F496E0D7535ACB2DC1" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">56-57</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E156EAB9CAC10760B2EBEB67E2698FA1" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">67</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="EC4B38B6FF3B4AE1FF9B114EB8451FA6" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">69</figureCitation>
) (parastylus 2.6 times the length of pedestal base, in lateral view the parastylus reach 0.37 of the length of forceps from base); 3) ventral knob on forceps base relatively small; 4) penis relatively thin at base (fused portion), not strongly expanded distally (Figs 
<figureCitation id="50F8451FD2CC63DDE939A66E4FD11FA9" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">56</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="EC608A2CD911FE43F488CD8FED1E449E" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">67</figureCitation>
); and 5) relatively dark species, head shaded stronger between lateral ocelli, occiput shaded gray except on pale medial line (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8607932758528F54ABCC91E097BA8515" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
). In the nymph: 1) inner protuberances on mandibular tusk almost contiguous (Figs 
<figureCitation id="B26ACD8F03EFC3E856C2A039287F34E7" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">59-61</figureCitation>
); 2) frontal tuft of setae with irregular sinuous form (arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="61036E6B9124774F00555CDDF50FFFCC" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">58</figureCitation>
); 3) ventral and dorsal projection at the apex of fore tarsus subequal in length (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A4D91BBCE1D6D7400738E9397FE803ED" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">63</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="4D4753EC83245F1E24BA6FD2C44C0EE2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Male imago</emphasis>
. Length (mm): body, 11.0; fore wing, 10.9-11.0; hind wing, 4.8; cerci, 28.0. General coloration yellowish white shaded with gray (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FAE6D0B4C19F581708BCBEC1C7B44BB9" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
). Head. Coloration yellowish white shaded widely with gray on dorsum, shaded stronger between lateral ocelli, except around median ocellus and hind margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="99D593267649B49C22671D81AF47C24A" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
). Antennae: scape and pedicel yellowish white completely shaded with gray, flagellum hyaline. Thorax. Pronotum with anterior ring hyaline, shaded with black posterolaterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0FF35E4FBBF2584C1C5032C24511C749" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
); posterior ring shaded gray except on sublateral areas and medial line. Mesonotum whitish yellow shaded with gray along medioparapsidal sutures and shaded with black on a V-shaped mark between posterior scutal protuberances (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D285C1E6306028FBDBDEA954F8A5FFB3" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
). Metanotum whitish yellow shaded gray medially. Thoracic pleura and sterna whitish yellow, with grayish small marks medially on furcasterna. Legs yellowish white shaded with grayish (fore legs broken off and lost). Wings: Membrane hyaline except basally slightly grayish, longitudinal and cross veins translucent shaded slightly with gray. Abdomen. Abdominal segments translucent-hyaline. Tergum I shaded gray anterolaterally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="E017E1073F0A6A063763B89CFFA279A4" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">65</figureCitation>
), terga II-IX shaded more extensively towards rear segments, except on: medial line of terga II-VII, and two pale marks (one submedian and one sublateral) in II-IX; tergum X shaded more completely with gray. Abdominal sterna shaded widely with brownish gray except on intersegmental membranes and around gill sclerites (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3704E4A6611485487B455EA9AC008FC8" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">66</figureCitation>
). Genitalia (Figs 
<figureCitation id="99F17ECEBA88BD732193A88E8F38E3A5" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">56-57</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="99BEAD02AD3A50A0699B831CF5DB3A62" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">67-69</figureCitation>
): sternum IX shaded with black on posterior margin and at both sides of the median furrow; relatively large parastyli orangeish, straight and long (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8AA7996BF1D2C549CF78130C832B2EB2" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">56</figureCitation>
); parastylus 2.6 times the length of pedestal base, in lateral view the parastylus reach 0.37 of the length of forceps from base; forceps and penis yellowish white, shaded gray on forceps. Caudal filament whitish translucent.
</paragraph>
<caption id="47C88FAB2129CB2440173DCE0937AD79" doi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" start="Figures 56–64" startId="F9">
<paragraph id="64E56B116999BC8038D4E24FC045A4B6" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis id="5C92C3BCD4FAA0A30417B11753BC02A3" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Figures 56-64.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="80EE2353492F7859E5223B520BA91668" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Dias &amp; Zúñiga" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tortopus coreguaje" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreguaje">
<emphasis id="B8A511A8DB9F31166CA27A9AB3A86F95" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tortopus coreguaje</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="074C02542227E8210EFD35013EDFFD2D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="409F139287DB7718BDAC813E38C37A10" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<emphasis id="2D229ADE55E2FC3835287CA202640E7B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Male nymph</emphasis>
(immature). Length: body, 9.5 mm; cerci, 2.5 mm; caudal filament, 2.0 mm. General coloration whitish shaded with gray (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BF005E17A300A708926D70E0F277594D" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">70</figureCitation>
). Head. Head shaded with gray in net-shaped pattern posteriorly to epicranial suture (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B2E7E497AB543B6108A195EAB7E0CEEC" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">70</figureCitation>
); anteriorly to this suture with two small lateral irregular-sinuous-shaped tufts of short setae (anterior to lateral ocelli, arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="59AE4EFE714AE9D9E5B989F67A164E6A" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">58</figureCitation>
); frontal ridge relatively straight in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B7963E8295BCC6AF351E1C9934C30352" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">58</figureCitation>
); fronto-clypeal region acutely projected medially (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C61E7B3971423D3DE0704F05E0492B34" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">58</figureCitation>
); a tuft of ca. 10 long setae basally to antennal condyle; and a group of 3 long setae anterior to eye and 6 long curved setae posterior to eye (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="100A62EDE13D74320042529530E98BB7" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">58</figureCitation>
). Mandibular tusks straight (Figs 
<figureCitation id="55BE03683B7731DFA8FC7C307A7D7540" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">59-61</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E61E8437A36693642235B83052F7E56F" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">70</figureCitation>
), with 2 subdistal rigid inner setae and ca. 12 weaker but long setae forming a basal arc (Figs 
<figureCitation id="DE712D598C5ED486213D07D4E215BBFE" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">59-61</figureCitation>
); inner margin with two large and contiguous tubercles, the subdistal directed ventrally and the submedian directed medially (Figs 
<figureCitation id="921CE95C8C55796C519EF66868FAFBDB" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">59-61</figureCitation>
), also a small blade-like projection present basally to distal spur (arrow in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F1259AD8C2F266AC30D3C1B270AAC16B" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">61</figureCitation>
). Maxillae with small triangular ventral gill. Hypopharynx and labium whitish. Thorax. Pronotum with narrow anterior ring (0.28 of total length of pronotum); antero-lateral corners acutely projected; shaded with black laterally on anterior ring and medially on posterior ring. Meso and metanotum shaded black medially except medial line; wingbuds whitish shaded gray only at base of costal area. Legs. Whitish with yellowish setae and sclerotized portions. Foreleg with tibia-tarsus flattened, remnants of the suture between tarsus and tibia visible, tarsal dorso-distal projection 0.5 of total length of claw (Figs 
<figureCitation id="E2C7FE500118D748047F26413A83EE5F" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">62-63</figureCitation>
); ventral surface of fore tibia with rows of long filtering setae as in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2F991ADB8D1CAB8B7CD15DB982488A88" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">62</figureCitation>
; fore femur with anterobasal short U-shaped row of filtering setae and an immediately posterior small group of ca. 7 long rigid and simple setae; apex of fore tarsus with ventral and dorsal projections subequal in length (but the ventral is much thinner, Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C50D7532D8583EF766FCE2375D47808D" captionStart="Figures 56–64" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 56 - 64. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago. 56, genitalia, ventral view (left forceps omitted); 57, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 58, head outline and setation, dorsal view (tusks omitted); 59, right mandible, inner view; 60, left mandible, inner view; 61, same, detail of apex (arrow indicates blade-like projection); 62, fore leg, ventral view (rows of filtering setae delineated); 63, fore tarsal claw; 64, hind tarsal claw." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures56-64" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550225" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">63</figureCitation>
). Middle leg with long setae on anterior and posterior (functionally ventral and dorsal, respectively) margins of femur, anterior margin of tibia and tarsus; apical third of tibia and tarsus completely covered with strong setae, apex of tibia with a brush of thick setae ventrally. Hind leg with short strong setae on posterior margin, and transverse subdistal row of short setae on dorsal surface; hind tibia and tarsus with long setae on posterior margin, anterior margin covered with short and strong setae. All tarsal claws slender and curved, without denticles. Abdomen (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D23F51F6BADACE9BADD2F75D06B2AC7C" captionStart="Figures 65–70" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 65 - 70. Tortopus coreguaje sp. nov., male imago: 65, general view, dorsal; 66, abdomen, ventral view; 67, genitalia, ventral view; 68, detail of parastylus (A = length of parastylus, B = length of pedestal); 69, genitalia, lateral view. Nymph: 70, general view, dorsal." figureDoi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">70</figureCitation>
). Gill I single, small and elongated, remaining gills well developed and double. Terga II-IX with medio-longitudinal row of setae; abdominal sterna with lateral margins strongly covered with setae, increasing in number posteriorly, sterna V-VI also with row of shorter setae on posterior margin; sternum IX with a row of few long setae on posterior half, along medial line. Cerci with rows of setae at each article, mainly on basal fourth; terminal filament much thinner and with whorls of setae almost on its entire length.
</paragraph>
<caption id="AF42B73171352885A56F5A7D2AAC6B6B" doi="10.3897/asp.79.e62735.figures65-70" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/550226" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" start="Figures 65–70" startId="F10">
